\begin_inset Formula $U_{2}^{low}(x,y)=2(x+y+kxy)-y^{2}$
\end_inset

, where the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

high
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

low
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 superscripts denote high cost vs low cost type.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The strategy space of each player are: 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{1}\equiv[0,\infty)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{2}\equiv\left\{ S_{2}^{low},S_{2}^{high}\right\} =\left\{ [0.\infty),[0,\infty)\right\} $
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Solving for each of player 2's best responses, we have:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula \begin{eqnarray}
y_{low}^{*} & = & \arg\max_{y}2(x+y+kxy)-y^{2}=1+kx\label{BNE1}\\
y_{high}^{*} & = & \arg\max_{y}2(x+y+kxy)-2y^{2}=\frac{1+kx}{2}\label{BNE2}\end{eqnarray}

\end_inset

Given these payoffs for player 2's two types, player 1 will maximize her
 expected utility to solve for 
\begin_inset Formula $x^{*}$
\end_inset

:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula \begin{eqnarray*}
x^{*} & = & \arg\max_{x}\left[\frac{1}{2}\left\{ 2(x+y_{low}^{*}+kxy_{low}^{*})-x^{2}\right\} +\frac{1}{2}\left\{ 2(x+y_{high}^{*}+kxy_{high}^{*})-x^{2}\right\} \right]\\
 & = & \arg\max_{x}\left[2x+y_{low}^{*}+y_{high}^{*}+kxy_{low}^{*}kxy_{high}^{*}-x^{2}\right].\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

FOCs (don't worry about K-T Conditions) result in the following:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula \begin{eqnarray*}
\frac{\partial U_{1}(x,y_{low}^{*},y_{high}^{*})}{\partial x}\mid_{x=x^{*}} & = & 2+ky_{low}^{*}+ky_{high}^{*}-2x^{*}=0\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
\therefore x^{*}=1+k\cdot\left(\frac{y_{low}^{*}+y_{high}^{*}}{2}\right).\label{BNE3}\end{equation}

